projects.name: Data Integration and Analytics Automation using SQL and Power BI
projects.description: Developed a robust data integration pipeline using SQL Server Integration Services (SSIS) in conjunction with .NET technologies. The pipeline will automate the extraction of data from both Excel spreadsheets and SQL Server databases, transforming and loading it into a unified data warehouse. Once integrated, Power BI is leveraged for generating insightful analytical reports and visualizations. This project aims to streamline data workflows, enhance data-driven decision-making capabilities, and optimize operational efficiencies through advanced analytics.

projects.description: - Technologies used: TensorFlow, scikit-learn, Pandas, NumPy, Matplotlib - Models trained on: Tuned KNN, Tuned Random Forest, Dense Neural Network, LSTM, ResNet, Autoencoder-Classifier. - Optimization Techniques used: Hyperparameter Tuning - Result: Highest accuracies achieved are 93% (ResNet), 92.5% (DNN), 91.6 (LSTM) - Uploaded the model using Flask, Docker and Github Actions. - Interactive web app uploaded on streamlit.
